# Page Structure and Routing

This project uses React Router for client-side routing and navigation.

## Routing Setup

- Routes are defined in [src/App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx)
- The app uses the latest React Router v6 with browser router
- Route guards check authentication state for protected routes

## Main Routes

- `/` - Home page
- `/strategy-report-genie` - Strategy Report Genie tool (main app feature)
- `/mt5-report-genie` - Legacy route redirecting to Strategy Report Genie
- `/courses` - Course listings
- `/pricing` - Pricing information
- `/contact` - Contact page
- `/privacy-policy` - Privacy policy
- `/terms-of-service` - Terms of service

## Page Components

Pages are organized in the `src/pages` directory:
- Each page is a React component that represents a complete view
- Pages compose smaller components to build complex UIs
- Example: [src/pages/StrategyReportGenie.tsx](mdc:src/pages/StrategyReportGenie.tsx)

## Navigation

- Primary navigation is handled by the [src/components/Navbar.tsx](mdc:src/components/Navbar.tsx) component
- Footer navigation is in [src/components/Footer.tsx](mdc:src/components/Footer.tsx)
- Both use React Router's `Link` component for client-side navigation

## Layout Structure

Most pages follow this layout structure:
1. Navbar at the top
2. Main content area
3. Footer at the bottom

The layout applies consistent spacing, styling, and responsive behavior across all pages.

